---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import TrustBar from "@/components/TrustBar.astro";
---
<Layout
  title="Shipping & Returns"
  description="Floof shipping times, free shipping threshold, and 30-day return policy for print-on-demand apparel."
>
  <section class="border-b border-floof-dark/6 bg-floof-sand/50">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-12 md:py-14">
      <p class="eyebrow">Policies</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold text-floof-dark">Shipping &amp; Returns</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-floof-dark/55">Clear policies so you can order with confidence.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <TrustBar compact />

  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-14 space-y-10">
    <section>
      <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-floof-dark">How shipping works</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-floof-dark/65 leading-relaxed">
        Every Floof piece is <strong class="text-floof-dark">print-on-demand</strong>. When you order, your item is printed and packed by our US fulfillment partner (Printful) — no warehouse sitting around in dusty boxes.
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-floof-dark/65 text-sm list-disc pl-5">
        <li><strong class="text-floof-dark">Production:</strong> typically 2–5 business days</li>
        <li><strong class="text-floof-dark">Transit (US):</strong> typically 3–7 business days after ship</li>
        <li><strong class="text-floof-dark">Free shipping:</strong> orders $75+ within the US</li>
        <li>You'll get tracking by email once your order ships</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-floof-dark">Returns & exchanges</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-floof-dark/65 leading-relaxed">
        We want you to love your Floof. You have <strong class="text-floof-dark">30 days</strong> from delivery to start a return on unworn items with tags attached.
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-floof-dark/65 text-sm list-disc pl-5">
        <li>Items must be clean, unworn, and in original condition</li>
        <li>Because products are made to order, we can't accept returns for buyer's remorse on custom-fit issues without trying sizing carefully first — use the size guide</li>
        <li>Defective or misprinted items: contact us and we'll make it right</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-floof-dark/65">
        Start a return: <a href="/contact" class="text-floof-pink underline">hello@floof.space</a> with your order number.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-floof-dark">Sizing tips</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-floof-dark/65 leading-relaxed">
        Most Floof apparel is unisex. Measure a shirt or hoodie you already love and compare to the size chart on each product page. If you're between sizes, we usually recommend sizing up for a relaxed fit.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="rounded-[1.25rem] bg-white p-8 outline outline-1 outline-floof-dark/6">
      <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-floof-dark">Still have questions?</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-floof-dark/60">We're a small SWFL brand — humans answer the inbox.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn mt-5">
        Contact us
      </a>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
